text: "You can either save your friends or you can save us all". This one line sums up every YA franchise on the planet, but it's interesting because it's the idea of maturation. Looking beyond yourself as opposed to when you were a child and you were in your little environment. I admit, I probably like "The Maze Runner" more than the other YA franchises. I suppose there has been something genuinely different about them and the only franchise to have a single director on all three so you have a consistent tone. I look forward to see how they end this. :)
